The paper deals with image segmentation using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel method for segmentation that uses binary encoding of CNN features, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses real-time segmentation, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses experiments to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which involves statistical analysis and evaluation, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
